  This is very different from other languages, so special attention should be paid.


* Boolean and logic operator

  Similar to Python, use "not" to reverse a boolean, and use "and" or "or" as logic operators.

  .image pic/123/7.png


* No null and undefine, only nil

  In Lua, there is no null or undefined, only nil, which is falcy.

